text:
Explain that when an aircraft that operates within controlled airspace needs to jettison fuel, the flight crew shall coordinate with Atc the following:
-   route to be flown which, if possible, should be clear of cities and towns, preferably over water and away from areas where thunderstorms have been reported or are expected;
-  the flight level to be used, which should be not less than 1 800 m (6 000 ft);
-  and the duration of fuel jettisoning.

